summary: This is a brief email from a US Attorney's Office in New York (USANYS) requesting contact information for the National trafficking coordinator who had reached out the previous day. It appears to be a routine administrative request related to human trafficking coordination.

keyFacts: The email was sent on February 26, 2019, from someone at the US Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York (USANYS).
The sender is requesting contact information for a National trafficking coordinator who had made contact the previous day.
This document shows communication within law enforcement regarding human trafficking coordination around the time of the Epstein investigation.
